author: johnh
msg: Rather than a single ContentRewriter being injected into the appropriate code paths, a ContentRewriterRegistry
is injected instead, enabling a list of ContentRewriters rather than only one.
By default, BasicContentRewriterRegistry is added, whose default constructor has a (pre-existing) ContentRewriter
instance injected into it, maintaining exact rewriting and execution semantics.
Rewriting code in HttpResponse and HttpRequest has been removed in favor of method-injection of ContentRewriterRegistry
into AbstractHttpCache, cleaning up code a bit. New test AbstractHttpCacheTest verifies proper rewriting behavior,
